\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Win rate vs.\ Kissat by satisfiability. UNSAT instances favor our coprocessor far more than SAT instances do. We attribute this to Kissat's aggressive phase saving / restarts being most useful on satisfiable inputs --- a heuristic edge that does not help when the proof must enumerate the whole tree.\relax }}{6}{table.caption.17}}
\newlabel{tab:sat-unsat}{{2}{6}{Win rate vs.\ Kissat by satisfiability. UNSAT instances favor our coprocessor far more than SAT instances do. We attribute this to Kissat's aggressive phase saving / restarts being most useful on satisfiable inputs --- a heuristic edge that does not help when the proof must enumerate the whole tree.\relax }{table.caption.17}{}}
